EXTRAORDINARY: BRICS, Vatican and Switzerland boycotted the Zelensky version. There is no call for Russia to withdraw from Ukraine

The BRICS countries, as well as the Vatican and Switzerland, refused to sign the final declaration of the so-called peace conference (in the "Zelensky" version) in Switzerland.
Key countries such as the Vatican, Saudi Arabia, Thailand, India, Mexico, South Africa, Brazil, and the UAE did not sign the document.
A boycott also came from Slovakia and Armenia.
The document was signed by 80 countries out of a total of 92 present.
The main theses of the declaration are three:
- nuclear power plants in Ukraine must operate under the full sovereign control of Ukraine;
- access to the seaports of the Black and Azov Seas must be restored;
- all prisoners of war must be released, and civilians must be returned to Ukraine;
It is striking that there is no call for the withdrawal of Russian troops from Ukraine, and this was the most important thing that Zelensky wanted to achieve. As is known, Russia did not participate in the peace conference, which nullified it in its infancy. There was no delegation from China either.

Southern Region has 7 out of 10 cyclone alerts in Brazil in the last ten years

Submerged houses in Lajeado (RS) this Wednesday (6) after a cyclone passed through. Recently affected by the formation of an extratropical cyclone in Rio Grande do Sul that killed more than 40 people, the southern region of the country registered 71 of the 92 alerts issued to the federal government in the last ten years due to this natural phenomenon. G1 analyzed data from the Integrated Disaster Information System, which receives daily alerts from Brazilian municipalities about the effects of natural phenomena. The system is linked to the Ministry of Integration and Regional Development. The South represents 77% of the alerts, due to the state of Santa Catarina, which registered 64 occurrences between January 2013 and August 2023. In the same period, five occurrences were registered in Rio Grande do Sul and two in Paraná. The city with the most cyclones was Balneário Barra do Sul (SC), with 13 episodes. See below a map with all the municipalities that issued a cyclone alert to the federal government in the last decade. Why in the South? Climatempo meteorologist Fábio Luengo explains that the southern states are historically more affected by extratropical cyclones due to their location in a zone where air masses meet. "It is a region that has a greater thermal contrast between the hot and humid air (coming from the North) and the cold air that comes from the South [of the planet]", he explains. What is unusual, says Luengo, is the intensity and frequency that these natural phenomena have gained. This week's extratropical cyclone, for example, marked the greatest natural tragedy in Rio Grande do Sul's history. Name three factors that explain this increase in extreme weather events. - Climate change, caused by human action on the planet, which increases the frequency and intensity of extreme weather events;

- Warming of the Atlantic Ocean, a process that is also more intense and frequent due to climate change;

- The action of the climate phenomenon called "El Niño", which, among other effects, causes excessive rain in the south of the country and the southeast of the country.
